article.headline: Drake 83, Chicago St. 53
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Josh Young scored 23 points as Drake beat Chicago State 83-53 Friday to advance to the championship game of the Drake Regency Classic. The Bulldogs (7-1), winning their sixth straight game, will play Texas-Pan American on Saturday in the title game. Leading 50-43, Drake went on an 11-2 run midway through the second half to build a 61-44 advantage. John Michael Hall, who finished with eight points, scored two baskets and Young connected on one of his six 3s during the spurt. Young hit 8 of 14 from the floor and was 6 of 11 behind the arc. John Cantrell led the Cougars with 20 points and David Holston added 19. The Bulldogs, coming off a 79-44 rout of Iowa State on Wednesday, built a 19-9 lead to open the game. They extended the lead to 30-14 after a 3 and a free throw by Young with 6:21 left in the first half. They led 38-31 at halftime. Jonathan Cox finished with 15 points and 10 rebounds for Drake, and Brent Heemskerk added 12. Drake is off to its best start since 1979-80.
